WEBVTT

00:08.921 --> 00:09.270
.

00:09.313 --> 00:11.098
- In the criminal justice
system,

00:11.141 --> 00:12.403
the people are represented

00:12.447 --> 00:15.145
by two separate,
yet equally important groups:

00:15.189 --> 00:17.060
the police,
who investigate crime,

00:17.104 --> 00:20.020
and the district attorneys,
who prosecute the offenders.

00:20.063 --> 00:21.760
These are their stories.

00:23.545 --> 00:26.156
- We need to go over
your schedule for next week.

00:26.200 --> 00:28.028
The Freedom Caucus is rallying
for the ban

00:28.071 --> 00:29.681
on trans athletes
in women's sports.

00:29.725 --> 00:31.118
They want you in D.C.
to support--

00:31.161 --> 00:33.033
- No, can we just talk
about this tomorrow?

00:33.076 --> 00:34.512
I am fried.

00:34.556 --> 00:36.210
- This is a great opportunity
for you to get attention

00:36.253 --> 00:38.125
from the national press.
We need to nail this down.

00:38.168 --> 00:40.301
- And we will, but right now,
all I wanna do

00:40.344 --> 00:43.347
is enjoy a nice glass
of red wine and some quiet.

00:43.391 --> 00:45.480
Today was supposed to be
my day off, remember?

00:45.523 --> 00:47.699
- I'm just doing my job.
- I know. I know.

00:47.743 --> 00:49.049
[glass crackles]

00:49.092 --> 00:51.138
[suspenseful music]

00:51.181 --> 00:53.488
What is that?

00:53.531 --> 00:54.924
Oh, my God.

00:54.967 --> 00:56.491
- We need to get you outside
and contact security.

00:56.534 --> 00:57.753
- Ryan?

00:59.929 --> 01:01.235
Ryan?

01:02.410 --> 01:03.933
- We really shouldn't be--

01:03.976 --> 01:11.071
♪

01:13.595 --> 01:15.423
- [screams]

01:16.989 --> 01:19.079
- DOA is Ryan Bartell, MD,

01:19.122 --> 01:21.342
owner and resident of the home.

01:21.385 --> 01:23.170
- Good lord.
- Brutal.

01:23.213 --> 01:25.781
Let me guess--
blunt force trauma?

01:25.824 --> 01:27.739
- There are multiple
lacerations on the front

01:27.783 --> 01:29.001
and side of his head.

01:29.045 --> 01:31.134
Looks like the killer
used that desk lamp.

01:31.178 --> 01:32.614
Swung it like a bat.

01:32.657 --> 01:34.877
- A lot of rage
to do that kind of damage.

01:34.920 --> 01:36.270
- Yeah, looks like our vic

01:36.313 --> 01:37.880
put up a good fight,
all things considered.

01:37.923 --> 01:40.404
- There appears to be skin and
blood under his fingernails.

01:40.448 --> 01:42.276
I bagged his hands.
- Time of death?

01:42.319 --> 01:44.408
- You're looking at sometime
late this morning,

01:44.452 --> 01:46.584
somewhere between 10:00 a.m.
and noon.

01:46.628 --> 01:47.890
- Detectives.

01:47.933 --> 01:50.021
Checked the doors
and windows like you asked.

01:50.066 --> 01:51.676
No sign of forced entry,

01:51.720 --> 01:54.418
but there are cameras covering
the front and rear entrances.

01:54.462 --> 01:55.593
- Okay.
Let's get the footage, yeah?

01:55.637 --> 01:56.985
- I just talked
to the congresswoman.

01:57.029 --> 01:58.944
Her head of security is
gonna send it over, ASAP.

01:58.988 --> 02:00.207
- Congresswoman?

02:00.250 --> 02:01.599
- Vic's wife
is Kristin Bartell,

02:01.643 --> 02:04.211
congresswoman
from the third district.

02:04.254 --> 02:05.560
- Really? Bartell.

02:05.603 --> 02:07.997
- She loves being
the center of attention.

02:08.039 --> 02:12.958
♪

02:13.002 --> 02:15.787
But I doubt this is the kind
of attention she had in mind.

02:17.746 --> 02:20.879
[dramatic music]

02:20.923 --> 02:27.843
♪

03:04.358 --> 03:06.795
- We were married for 15 years.

03:06.838 --> 03:08.231
He was my whole world.

03:08.275 --> 03:10.190
I don't--I don't know.

03:12.453 --> 03:13.802
- Congresswoman,
do you know anybody

03:13.845 --> 03:15.238
who wanted to harm
your husband?

03:15.282 --> 03:18.023
- This isn't about him.

03:18.067 --> 03:20.025
He was a saint.

03:20.069 --> 03:21.418
This is about me.

03:21.462 --> 03:24.291
This is about
my political views.

03:24.334 --> 03:26.206
This is my fault.

03:26.249 --> 03:27.555
- What do you mean,
it's your fault?

03:27.598 --> 03:28.904
- That was supposed to be me.

03:28.947 --> 03:30.558
I was scheduled
to be here all day,

03:30.601 --> 03:32.516
but I got called
into the office last minute

03:32.560 --> 03:34.170
for an emergency
committee meeting.

03:34.214 --> 03:37.304
- What makes you so sure that
you were the intended target?

03:37.347 --> 03:39.741
- I'm a conservative
congresswoman in a state

03:39.784 --> 03:43.440
where admitting that out loud
is a mortal sin.

03:43.484 --> 03:45.616
I'm constantly
receiving threats.

03:45.660 --> 03:47.227
In the minds
of far-left activists,

03:47.270 --> 03:49.316
I'm literally the devil.

03:49.359 --> 03:51.579
- Any of those threats
stand out in particular?

03:53.233 --> 03:54.756
- Last week,
there was an email.

03:56.758 --> 04:00.414
And they said that they would
kill me in my own home.

04:03.721 --> 04:05.070
- Do you know who sent that?

04:05.114 --> 04:06.898
- No.

04:06.942 --> 04:08.552
It was anonymous.

04:08.596 --> 04:10.554
I just--I flagged the message
for my security team.

04:15.167 --> 04:17.692
- "You won't know when, but one
day soon, you'll turn around,

04:17.735 --> 04:20.216
and I'll be there,
in your house,

04:20.260 --> 04:21.913
with no one around
to save you."

04:21.957 --> 04:24.960
Message sent from an IP address
registered in your name.

04:25.003 --> 04:26.701
- Yeah, I sent it.

04:26.744 --> 04:29.225
I should probably know better,
but frankly, she deserved it.

04:29.269 --> 04:30.313
- How's that?

04:30.357 --> 04:31.575
- I'm a drag queen.

04:31.619 --> 04:34.317
I started a program,
Read the House Down.

04:34.361 --> 04:36.406
Once a week,
me and other queens

04:36.450 --> 04:39.409
volunteer to read to kids
from the community.

04:39.453 --> 04:41.019
- You do it in drag?

04:41.063 --> 04:43.239
- Well, the idea is to get
kids excited about reading

04:43.283 --> 04:45.023
by making it fun.

04:45.067 --> 04:48.026
- Aren't drag queens
more of an--an adult thing?

04:48.070 --> 04:50.332
- Drag is just a celebration
of who you are.

04:50.377 --> 04:52.466
The kids love it.
It makes it fun.

04:52.509 --> 04:53.945
- There's nothing fun
about sending a threat

04:53.989 --> 04:56.034
to that congresswoman.
- I was being dramatic.

04:56.078 --> 04:58.907
But Bartell introduced a bill
that would ban children

04:58.950 --> 05:00.561
from being exposed
to drag queens.

05:00.604 --> 05:02.258
It's a coded way
of telling the crazies

05:02.302 --> 05:03.520
out there
that we're pedophiles.

05:03.564 --> 05:05.522
It sparked all kinds
of online hate,

05:05.566 --> 05:07.568
so I thought she should
know what it felt like.

05:07.611 --> 05:09.744
- You seem angry.
- Damn right I am.

05:09.787 --> 05:11.615
- Angry enough to show up
at Kristin Bartell's

05:11.659 --> 05:12.964
house yesterday morning?

05:13.008 --> 05:14.531
- I would never actually
do anything like that.

05:14.575 --> 05:15.663
I'm a pacifist.

05:15.706 --> 05:17.229
- All the same, where were you

05:17.273 --> 05:19.275
yesterday morning
at 10:00 a.m.?

05:19.319 --> 05:20.798
- [sighs]

05:20.842 --> 05:22.496
- Dwayne Washington
was at a photo shoot

05:22.539 --> 05:24.541
for his literacy program
at the time of the murder.

05:24.585 --> 05:26.891
- Wow, that's some
great contouring.

05:26.935 --> 05:29.807
- Hmm.
- But where does that leave us?

05:29.851 --> 05:34.595
I'm being hounded by City Hall,
One PP, Capitol Police, it's--

05:34.638 --> 05:36.901
- M.E. was able to retrieve DNA

05:36.945 --> 05:38.468
from under Bartell's
fingernails,

05:38.512 --> 05:39.991
but there's no match
in the system.

05:40.034 --> 05:42.429
- Okay, what about footage
from the security cameras?

05:42.472 --> 05:43.691
- Still waiting on
the congresswoman's

05:43.734 --> 05:45.040
people to send it over.

05:45.082 --> 05:46.389
- We're combing
through all the threats

05:46.433 --> 05:47.477
she's received
in the past few months

05:47.521 --> 05:48.913
to see if any of them
seem credible.

05:48.957 --> 05:51.307
- I've got something
interesting.

05:51.351 --> 05:54.005
I've been going through the
street cam footage we pulled.

05:54.049 --> 05:55.964
This car shows up
at an intersection

05:56.007 --> 05:58.096
near the crime scene
multiple times

05:58.140 --> 05:59.402
the morning of the murder.

05:59.446 --> 06:01.491
- So it's circling the block?

06:01.535 --> 06:02.927
- It looks that way.

06:02.971 --> 06:06.627
And check this--the car
belongs to a Paul Koening.

06:06.670 --> 06:09.238
Multiple arrests for rioting,
inciting violence,

06:09.281 --> 06:10.674
and stalking.

06:10.718 --> 06:13.068
- All right, guys.
You know what to do.

06:13.111 --> 06:16.027
[suspenseful music]

06:16.071 --> 06:17.812
♪

06:17.855 --> 06:19.727
- Okay, I have
your oat milk cappuccino.

06:19.770 --> 06:22.207
Here you go.
- Thank you.

06:22.251 --> 06:23.687
- NYPD.

06:23.731 --> 06:25.907
We need to talk to the owner,
Paul Koening.

06:25.950 --> 06:26.864
- He's not here.

06:26.908 --> 06:28.518
- Know where we can find him?

06:28.562 --> 06:30.477
- Nah, man.
I just work here.

06:30.520 --> 06:33.828
[clattering, rustling]

06:33.871 --> 06:35.003
- Mind if we take
a look around?

06:35.046 --> 06:36.483
- I--I don't know, I think,
uh--

06:36.526 --> 06:38.659
don't you have to have
a warrant or whatever?

06:43.011 --> 06:44.752
- You wouldn't be Paul,
would you?

06:44.795 --> 06:45.883
NYPD.

06:50.758 --> 06:52.194
- Where are you
running to, Paul?

06:52.237 --> 06:53.587
- I didn't do anything.

06:57.068 --> 06:58.505
- You sure about that?

07:06.861 --> 07:07.078
.

07:07.122 --> 07:08.993
- Some interesting
reading material

07:09.037 --> 07:10.691
you got there
in your bag, Paul.

07:10.734 --> 07:14.129
You Antifa folks
got a real way with words.

07:14.172 --> 07:15.957
- Quite the artist, too, huh?

07:16.000 --> 07:17.959
- You are part
of Antifa, right?

07:18.002 --> 07:19.874
- It's not a group you join

07:19.917 --> 07:22.006
with membership fees
or whatever.

07:22.050 --> 07:23.791
It's a political stance,
an understanding

07:23.834 --> 07:25.445
of what's right or wrong.

07:25.488 --> 07:26.576
- Oh, so you think it's right

07:26.620 --> 07:28.186
to murder
a politician's husband?

07:28.230 --> 07:30.014
- I had nothing to do with what
happened to Ryan Bartell.

07:30.058 --> 07:33.582
- Paul, we got video of you
in the neighborhood

07:33.627 --> 07:36.194
of a U.S. congresswoman whose
husband was beaten to death,

07:36.238 --> 07:38.153
five minutes before his murder.

07:38.196 --> 07:39.720
And we just caught you
walking around

07:39.763 --> 07:41.461
with a nightstick
and devil photos

07:41.504 --> 07:42.810
of the same congresswoman.

07:42.853 --> 07:43.898
Do the math.

07:43.941 --> 07:45.203
- Enlighten me here, Paul.

07:45.247 --> 07:48.555
You get to her house,
she's not there,

07:48.598 --> 07:50.861
so you murdered the husband?

07:50.905 --> 07:53.211
He was a family doctor.
Why did he deserve that?

07:53.255 --> 07:55.823
- I never went
inside the house.

07:55.866 --> 07:57.302
I was just checking
out the area

07:57.346 --> 07:59.391
because we were planning
a peaceful protest

07:59.435 --> 08:00.958
outside of Bartell's home.

08:01.002 --> 08:03.178
- You wanna protest outside
of a private residence

08:03.221 --> 08:05.180
with a baton, and you
wanna call it peaceful?

08:05.223 --> 08:07.443
- Politicians like
Kristin Bartell

08:07.487 --> 08:09.837
want to insert themselves
into the private lives

08:09.880 --> 08:11.882
of every citizen
in the country.

08:11.926 --> 08:13.797
So why shouldn't their
personal space be fair game?

08:13.841 --> 08:15.669
- If you didn't do
anything wrong,

08:15.712 --> 08:17.714
why did you try to run?

08:17.758 --> 08:19.716
- Because I don't
trust the police.

08:19.760 --> 08:21.762
- Submit to a DNA test.

08:21.805 --> 08:23.459
- And help an
authoritarian state

08:23.503 --> 08:25.809
catalog my biological data?

08:25.853 --> 08:27.376
Go to hell.

08:27.419 --> 08:29.509
- Choice number two is,
we charge you with murder.

08:32.424 --> 08:33.424
- Hey, Lou.

08:33.469 --> 08:34.644
We put a rush
on Koening's DNA--

08:34.688 --> 08:35.863
not a match.

08:35.905 --> 08:37.255
- And the lab wasn't able
to find

08:37.299 --> 08:39.213
any traces of blood
on the baton.

08:39.256 --> 08:41.085
- So he's not our killer.
- Doesn't look like it.

08:41.129 --> 08:43.827
- All right. Cut him loose.

08:43.871 --> 08:46.874
Hey, did Bartell's
security team ever

08:46.917 --> 08:48.789
send over the footage
from the brownstone?

08:48.832 --> 08:51.095
- You know, Vi's followed up
with them a couple of times,

08:51.139 --> 08:52.619
but we haven't gotten anything.

08:52.662 --> 08:54.969
- Why don't you pay a
visit to the congresswoman

08:55.012 --> 08:56.144
and see what the holdup is?

09:00.322 --> 09:03.891
- This is all of the footage
from the front

09:03.934 --> 09:06.894
and back door cameras
from the last six months.

09:06.937 --> 09:08.156
- Thank you.

09:08.199 --> 09:10.201
- I apologize for the delay,

09:10.245 --> 09:12.160
but we had
a little complication

09:12.203 --> 09:13.770
we were trying to sort out.

09:13.814 --> 09:15.729
- What kind of complication?

09:15.772 --> 09:18.993
- Well, the footage that you're
probably most interested in--

09:19.036 --> 09:21.473
footage from the morning
that Ryan was murdered--

09:21.517 --> 09:22.474
doesn't exist.

09:23.954 --> 09:25.608
- Why is that?

09:25.652 --> 09:26.914
- Someone shut down the system.

09:26.957 --> 09:29.307
- Someone? The killer?

09:29.351 --> 09:30.744
- No.

09:30.787 --> 09:33.007
My husband.

09:33.050 --> 09:35.618
- Now, why would he do that?

09:35.662 --> 09:37.185
- Well, I'm not sure,

09:37.228 --> 09:39.448
but I do know that he
occasionally sees patients

09:39.491 --> 09:41.537
in his home office,
and for some of them,

09:41.581 --> 09:44.758
he deactivates the cameras
for privacy reasons.

09:44.801 --> 09:47.717
[suspenseful music]

09:47.761 --> 09:51.068
♪

09:51.112 --> 09:53.027
- Dr. Bartell was
such a good man.

09:53.070 --> 09:54.637
It makes me sick to my
stomach when I think

09:54.681 --> 09:55.943
about what happened to him.

09:55.986 --> 09:57.771
- Sorry for your loss.

09:57.814 --> 09:59.076
When was the last time
you saw him?

09:59.120 --> 10:01.644
- Um, the morning
he was killed,

10:01.688 --> 10:02.819
he called to say
that he wouldn't

10:02.863 --> 10:04.908
be in until the afternoon.

10:04.952 --> 10:05.996
- Was that unusual?

10:06.040 --> 10:07.607
- Uh, not really.

10:07.650 --> 10:09.609
If he only had paperwork or
patient follow-up calls to do,

10:09.652 --> 10:11.698
he often just did it
from his home office.

10:11.741 --> 10:13.961
I'm pretty sure I can access
his personal calendar,

10:14.004 --> 10:15.136
if you want me to check that.

10:15.179 --> 10:16.572
- That would be very helpful.

10:16.616 --> 10:18.269
- Thank you.

10:23.013 --> 10:24.928
Huh. That's odd.

10:24.972 --> 10:26.321
- What's odd?

10:26.364 --> 10:27.975
- Uh, he has
an appointment blocked out

10:28.018 --> 10:29.324
at 11:00 a.m. that day,

10:29.367 --> 10:31.413
but there's no patient name
listed.

10:31.456 --> 10:33.589
Just the letters TM.

10:33.633 --> 10:35.199
- I take it that's unusual?

10:38.681 --> 10:40.988
Bartell's assistant went
back over his calendar

10:41.031 --> 10:42.685
and found
four other appointments

10:42.729 --> 10:45.079
with the letters TM
over the past three months.

10:45.122 --> 10:46.994
- Vi's going over
the security footage now

10:47.037 --> 10:48.256
from the brownstone
to see if the cameras

10:48.299 --> 10:49.736
were turned on
for any of those.

10:49.779 --> 10:52.913
- Now, whether TM are initials
or some kind of code,

10:52.956 --> 10:54.349
add that
to the turned-off cameras--

10:54.392 --> 10:56.351
- Bartell was hiding something.
- Yeah.

10:56.394 --> 10:58.135
And whatever it was,
likely what got him killed.

10:58.179 --> 11:00.094
- My money's on an affair.

11:00.137 --> 11:01.486
- You got anything?

11:01.530 --> 11:02.705
- Possibly.

11:02.749 --> 11:04.359
Bartell consistently
turned off the feeds

11:04.402 --> 11:06.187
before each
of these TM meetings,

11:06.230 --> 11:07.884
but it looks like
he didn't start doing that

11:07.928 --> 11:09.364
until after the first one.

11:09.407 --> 11:11.845
- So do you have video
of the suspect?

11:11.888 --> 11:13.324
- The appointment was at 11:00.

11:13.368 --> 11:15.849
So that's right about here.

11:15.892 --> 11:22.029
♪

11:22.072 --> 11:23.552
- That's a child.

11:23.595 --> 11:25.554
- He can't be more
than 12 or 13.

11:34.432 --> 11:34.781
.

11:34.824 --> 11:36.521
- Do you recognize this kid?

11:36.565 --> 11:39.873
- Uh, that is our
school uniform.

11:39.915 --> 11:42.745
Yes. That's Taylor Myers.

11:42.789 --> 11:44.616
- TM.

11:44.660 --> 11:45.966
We need to speak to Taylor.

11:46.009 --> 11:47.968
- He should still probably
be in his advisory.

11:48.011 --> 11:49.012
I can take you there.

11:49.056 --> 11:50.231
- What grade is he in?

11:50.274 --> 11:51.580
- Uh, he's in the
seventh grade.

11:51.623 --> 11:54.017
Um--
[bell rings]

11:54.061 --> 11:55.410
Unfortunately,
he had to repeat a year

11:55.453 --> 11:58.935
due to a extended absence
last spring.

11:58.979 --> 12:01.503
He's been struggling.
Mental health issues.

12:01.546 --> 12:03.157
- Oh.

12:03.200 --> 12:06.508
Has Taylor ever shown any signs
of violent tendencies?

12:06.551 --> 12:08.031
- Not to my knowledge.

12:08.075 --> 12:09.729
At least,
not directed towards others.

12:09.772 --> 12:12.383
Oh, there he is. Taylor.

12:12.427 --> 12:13.733
- Taylor Myers.

12:13.776 --> 12:15.299
Can we have a word?

12:15.343 --> 12:17.693
- Hey, kid.

12:17.737 --> 12:19.695
- I'll take the side.

12:19.739 --> 12:22.698
[tense music]

12:22.742 --> 12:28.573
♪

12:28.617 --> 12:29.661
- Kid, no!

12:29.705 --> 12:31.446
[tires screech]
[horn honks]

12:34.754 --> 12:37.017
You okay?

12:37.060 --> 12:38.540
What were you thinking?

12:45.242 --> 12:46.722
- Taylor, right?

12:46.766 --> 12:52.989
Uh, what was your relationship
with, uh, Ryan Bartell?

12:53.033 --> 12:55.383
- I--I didn't have one.

12:55.426 --> 12:56.645
I don't know who that is.

12:56.688 --> 12:58.778
- Oh, uh...

12:58.821 --> 13:02.607
that's you three months ago,

13:02.651 --> 13:04.958
going into his house.

13:05.001 --> 13:07.569
- Uh, uh...

13:07.612 --> 13:09.614
I was selling gift cards
for a fundraiser at school.

13:09.658 --> 13:14.271
I--I knocked on a bunch
of people's doors that day.

13:14.315 --> 13:17.013
- Taylor, we know that you were
in that house for 40 minutes.

13:17.057 --> 13:19.233
It doesn't take that long
to sell gift cards.

13:26.283 --> 13:28.982
- Oh, that house. That guy.

13:29.025 --> 13:30.853
Yeah, he was--
he was super talkative.

13:30.897 --> 13:34.770
I mean, he--he talked forever.
I just didn't get his name.

13:34.814 --> 13:36.467
I never saw him
again after that.

13:38.513 --> 13:41.298
- Okay.

13:41.342 --> 13:43.170
Listen.

13:43.213 --> 13:48.305
If this man hurt you
in any way,

13:48.349 --> 13:50.830
you can tell us.

13:50.873 --> 13:52.832
It's okay.

13:52.875 --> 13:55.573
[apprehensive music]

13:55.617 --> 13:57.924
♪

13:57.967 --> 13:59.142
You're safe here.

13:59.186 --> 14:01.492
You can tell us what happened.

14:01.536 --> 14:03.016
- He didn't.

14:08.021 --> 14:09.631
- That's enough.

14:09.674 --> 14:11.807
He's answered your questions,
so if there's nothing else--

14:11.851 --> 14:13.417
- Yeah, we'd like to get
a DNA sample

14:13.461 --> 14:14.941
so we can rule him out
as a suspect.

14:14.984 --> 14:16.899
- Absolutely not.
My son has done nothing wrong.

14:16.943 --> 14:18.858
He was at school
when that man was murdered.

14:18.901 --> 14:20.511
We're leaving now.

14:26.474 --> 14:27.431
- [sighs]

14:30.565 --> 14:33.046
- I just spoke to the school
to verify Taylor's attendance

14:33.089 --> 14:34.786
on the day of the murder.
- And?

14:34.830 --> 14:37.224
- Taylor was marked as present
during advisory that day,

14:37.267 --> 14:39.139
but according to Taylor's
math teacher,

14:39.182 --> 14:41.445
whose class is
from 11:00 to 11:50,

14:41.489 --> 14:42.969
Taylor was pulled out
for a session

14:43.012 --> 14:44.100
with the school counselor.

14:44.144 --> 14:45.319
- Did you check
with the counselor

14:45.362 --> 14:46.973
to see if Taylor was there?

14:47.016 --> 14:48.931
- I haven't been able
to get ahold of her

14:48.975 --> 14:50.540
because she's been on
bereavement leave

14:50.585 --> 14:52.195
the past two days.

14:52.239 --> 14:54.676
The school counselor
is Susan Bartell.

14:54.719 --> 14:56.417
- Bartell?

14:56.460 --> 15:00.334
- Her brother is...
- Ryan Bartell, our vic.

15:04.251 --> 15:05.600
- Taylor is a great kid.

15:05.643 --> 15:08.385
This is obviously
some kind of mistake.

15:08.429 --> 15:09.952
Taylor would never hurt anyone.

15:09.996 --> 15:11.258
- Just answer the question,
please.

15:11.301 --> 15:15.131
Was Taylor Myers
in your office, Ms. Bartell,

15:15.175 --> 15:17.177
at 11:00 a.m. the day
your brother was murdered?

15:20.571 --> 15:23.052
- Okay.
Do you know where he was?

15:24.706 --> 15:26.229
- If you know anything
that went down

15:26.273 --> 15:27.491
and you don't tell us,

15:27.535 --> 15:29.406
you could be an accomplice
to murder.

15:29.450 --> 15:31.017
- I'm telling you,
Taylor would never hurt--

15:31.060 --> 15:32.409
- And we're telling you,
answer the question.

15:32.453 --> 15:33.889
- I don't know
where Taylor was.

15:33.933 --> 15:35.195
- Why not?
You signed him out.

15:35.238 --> 15:37.066
He should be with you.

15:37.110 --> 15:38.546
- It's not what you think.

15:38.589 --> 15:40.069
- I hope it's not what I think,
because what I think

15:40.113 --> 15:42.593
is that you were
funneling a little boy

15:42.637 --> 15:45.248
to your brother's home
in secret.

15:45.292 --> 15:47.207
- Please.
Ryan wasn't molesting Taylor.

15:47.250 --> 15:48.686
He was treating her.

15:48.730 --> 15:52.516
[suspenseful music]

15:52.560 --> 15:54.910
- Her?

15:54.954 --> 15:56.477
- Yes.

15:58.479 --> 16:00.220
Taylor is trans.

16:00.263 --> 16:02.918
She's known
she was a girl since--

16:02.962 --> 16:06.530
well, for her whole life,
really.

16:06.574 --> 16:09.142
I've been counseling Taylor
for years now.

16:09.185 --> 16:11.448
She's had a really tough time.

16:11.492 --> 16:15.148
- So what do you mean by your
brother was treating her?

16:15.191 --> 16:16.584
- As puberty
started kicking in,

16:16.627 --> 16:19.456
Taylor's gender dysphoria
got worse.

16:19.500 --> 16:21.893
She was hurting herself,
and it got so bad

16:21.937 --> 16:23.547
we feared for her life.

16:23.591 --> 16:27.247
But her parents forbid her from
transitioning, even socially.

16:27.290 --> 16:30.511
- So your doctor brother
was helping her, what,

16:30.554 --> 16:32.687
with gender reassignment
or something?

16:32.730 --> 16:35.559
- No, nothing surgical
or permanent.

16:35.603 --> 16:40.042
I just asked him to provide her
with gender-affirming care.

16:40.086 --> 16:41.087
- I'm sorry.

16:41.130 --> 16:42.784
What does that mean, exactly?

16:42.827 --> 16:45.308
- He was giving her medication
to block her hormones.

16:45.352 --> 16:47.745
It's a pause button
for puberty.

16:47.789 --> 16:50.400
It's to provide relief
for trans youth

16:50.444 --> 16:54.361
who feel distress going
through the wrong puberty.

16:54.404 --> 16:55.884
- Let me get this straight.

16:55.927 --> 16:58.539
You conspired with your brother
to medically intervene

16:58.582 --> 17:01.585
in a child's care
without the parents' consent?

17:01.629 --> 17:03.631
- I was respecting
her personhood.

17:03.674 --> 17:05.546
The medication
has been used for decades

17:05.589 --> 17:08.417
to help non-trans children
who begin puberty too early.

17:08.462 --> 17:11.073
If, for whatever reason,
she changes her mind,

17:11.117 --> 17:13.075
she just stops
taking the medication

17:13.118 --> 17:14.337
and puberty kicks in.

17:14.381 --> 17:16.905
It is completely safe
and reversible.

17:16.948 --> 17:18.993
- Your brother is dead.

17:19.038 --> 17:20.691
So what you did
wasn't that safe.

17:20.734 --> 17:23.694
And the last time I checked,
death isn't reversible.

17:26.522 --> 17:28.176
No one's got a right
to get between

17:28.221 --> 17:29.700
a parent and their child.

17:29.744 --> 17:31.572
- She had a student in crisis.
She made a judgment call.

17:31.615 --> 17:33.878
- It's not her call to make.
- That I get.

17:33.922 --> 17:35.141
What I don't get is,

17:35.184 --> 17:37.099
if Dr. Bartell was trying
to help Taylor,

17:37.143 --> 17:38.535
then why would she try
to kill him?

17:38.579 --> 17:40.102
- Who knows?
Maybe violent outbursts

17:40.146 --> 17:41.495
are a side effect of the meds.

17:41.538 --> 17:43.366
A lot can go wrong when
you're secretly pumping

17:43.410 --> 17:44.715
hormones into a teenager.

17:44.759 --> 17:46.326
- That theory
doesn't hold, bro,

17:46.369 --> 17:48.154
because they weren't pumping
hormones into a teenager.

17:48.197 --> 17:49.720
The medication
was actually blocking it.

17:49.764 --> 17:52.723
- Whatever the answer,
now we have enough evidence

17:52.767 --> 17:55.639
to demand Taylor's DNA.

17:55.683 --> 17:58.599
[tense music]

17:58.642 --> 18:01.167
♪

18:01.210 --> 18:02.385
- What are you doing here?

18:05.127 --> 18:07.086
Why did you let them in?

18:07.129 --> 18:08.826
- I didn't have a choice.

18:08.870 --> 18:11.264
- There is no way
Taylor's DNA was a match.

18:13.179 --> 18:16.138
- I--I told you the truth.
I didn't do anything, I swear.

18:16.182 --> 18:18.271
- It's okay, Taylor.
Your dad's right.

18:18.314 --> 18:20.011
Your DNA was not a match.
- Then leave us alone.

18:20.055 --> 18:21.143
This is harassment.

18:21.187 --> 18:22.579
- We're here to talk
to you, actually.

18:22.623 --> 18:24.929
- Yeah, the markers
on Taylor's DNA

18:24.973 --> 18:28.150
indicate that we're looking
for a close male relative.

18:31.197 --> 18:32.937
- Roll up your sleeves, please.

18:32.981 --> 18:39.422
♪

18:41.207 --> 18:42.382
Turn your hands over.

18:49.432 --> 18:51.173
- I want a lawyer.

18:51.217 --> 18:52.827
- You can call one
down at the station.

18:56.309 --> 18:58.963
- Turn around.

18:59.007 --> 19:01.140
[handcuffs clicking]

19:01.183 --> 19:06.884
♪

19:11.802 --> 19:11.976
.

19:12.020 --> 19:14.109
- Calling docket
ending in 9870,

19:14.153 --> 19:15.806
the People versus Robert Myers,

19:15.850 --> 19:18.200
alleging murder
in the second degree.

19:18.244 --> 19:19.854
- People on bail?

19:19.897 --> 19:21.943
- We have substantial evidence
that the defendant

19:21.986 --> 19:25.468
murdered a beloved physician
in his own home.

19:25.512 --> 19:27.557
No amount of bail is sufficient

19:27.601 --> 19:29.211
to guarantee his return
to court.

19:29.255 --> 19:30.821
People seek remand.

19:30.865 --> 19:32.345
- Ms. Dumont?

19:32.388 --> 19:33.650
- Robert Myers is
a hard-working working

19:33.694 --> 19:35.739
family man
with no criminal history.

19:35.783 --> 19:37.741
He's lived in the same home
with his wife and son

19:37.785 --> 19:40.222
for over a decade.
He is not a flight risk.

19:40.266 --> 19:43.356
- Your Honor, the likelihood
of a conviction is strong.

19:43.399 --> 19:45.314
DNA will put the defendant
at the scene.

19:45.358 --> 19:46.924
- We'll stipulate
to the forensics.

19:46.968 --> 19:49.710
We plan to offer the defense
of justification.

19:49.753 --> 19:53.496
Ryan Bartell gave dangerous
and life-altering medications

19:53.540 --> 19:54.758
to my client's child.

19:54.802 --> 19:56.847
When my client informed Bartell

19:56.891 --> 19:58.588
that he was gonna notify
the authorities,

19:58.632 --> 19:59.894
Bartell attacked him.

19:59.937 --> 20:01.809
He was simply
defending himself.

20:01.852 --> 20:03.332
- You can argue
all that at trial.

20:03.376 --> 20:05.421
Until then,
defendant is remanded.

20:05.465 --> 20:06.466
Next case.

20:06.509 --> 20:08.381
[gavel bangs]

20:08.424 --> 20:10.557
- Myers is claiming
self-defense.

20:10.600 --> 20:12.646
- Any violence in Myers's past?

20:12.689 --> 20:14.517
- There was a prior incident

20:14.561 --> 20:16.432
in his daughter's school
a few months ago.

20:16.476 --> 20:18.478
Myers flipped out
when confronted

20:18.521 --> 20:21.263
with Taylor's gender dysphoria.
- What did he do?

20:21.307 --> 20:23.178
- Well, he smashed
the counselor,

20:23.222 --> 20:24.527
Susan Bartell's laptop.

20:24.571 --> 20:26.181
He threw a coffee mug

20:26.225 --> 20:27.704
and shoved her up
against the wall.

20:27.748 --> 20:29.184
- Okay.

20:29.228 --> 20:30.968
Establishes he's got a temper.

20:31.012 --> 20:33.449
- And that his daughter's
gender dysphoria

20:33.493 --> 20:35.190
is the trigger for that temper.

20:35.234 --> 20:36.452
- Yeah, at the same time,

20:36.496 --> 20:37.975
Bartell's actions
are hard to defend.

20:38.019 --> 20:40.151
He was giving medication
to a 13-year-old child

20:40.195 --> 20:41.762
without her parents' consent.

20:41.805 --> 20:44.460
- He was a physician
doing what he believed

20:44.504 --> 20:46.549
to be in his patient's
best interest.

20:46.593 --> 20:47.898
- I'm not sure that matters.

20:47.942 --> 20:50.640
- Either way,
he didn't deserve to die.

20:50.684 --> 20:52.512
Make that clear
in your opening.

20:59.345 --> 21:04.350
- Dr. Ryan Bartell practiced
medicine for over two decades.

21:04.393 --> 21:06.613
He cared very much
about his patients.

21:06.656 --> 21:10.007
And unfortunately,
that's the reason

21:10.051 --> 21:12.401
he was brutally murdered.

21:12.445 --> 21:14.011
The evidence in this case
will show that

21:14.055 --> 21:17.493
the defendant beat Dr. Bartell
to death with a desk lamp--

21:17.537 --> 21:20.366
hit him more than 20 times.

21:20.409 --> 21:21.889
Why?

21:21.932 --> 21:23.760
Because Dr. Bartell
was treating

21:23.804 --> 21:27.242
his transgender daughter
with puberty blockers.

21:27.286 --> 21:31.594
Now, I understand that
the use of this medication

21:31.638 --> 21:33.422
might not sit right
with everyone.

21:33.466 --> 21:36.643
And we are certainly all
entitled to our opinions,

21:36.686 --> 21:38.819
although it is important
to know

21:38.862 --> 21:40.864
the American Medical
Association

21:40.908 --> 21:43.824
has deemed
gender-affirming care

21:43.867 --> 21:47.001
for children like her
not only safe,

21:47.044 --> 21:49.743
but medically necessary.

21:49.786 --> 21:53.486
But ladies and gentlemen,

21:53.529 --> 21:55.401
no matter what you believe

21:55.444 --> 21:57.185
about Taylor's course
of treatment,

21:57.228 --> 22:01.363
you must believe one thing.

22:01.407 --> 22:04.627
This is murder.

22:04.671 --> 22:09.458
Savage, brutal, and senseless.

22:09.502 --> 22:11.634
The person who inflicted
these injuries

22:11.678 --> 22:15.725
must be held responsible.

22:15.769 --> 22:20.034
And that person is
sitting right over there.

22:20.077 --> 22:23.037
[tense music]

22:23.080 --> 22:28.738
♪

22:28.782 --> 22:31.654
- Ryan Bartell was an activist,

22:31.698 --> 22:35.179
a doctor who preyed
on a confused child

22:35.223 --> 22:38.748
in order to further
his own liberal agenda.

22:38.792 --> 22:41.403
What the evidence
will actually show

22:41.447 --> 22:43.666
is that Ryan Bartell

22:43.710 --> 22:46.669
illegally prescribed
dangerous medications.

22:46.713 --> 22:49.498
He never sought or received
parental consent

22:49.542 --> 22:53.328
and implemented unproven
and highly controversial

22:53.372 --> 22:54.808
medical treatments.

22:54.851 --> 22:58.289
Said another way,
Ryan Bartell was a criminal

22:58.333 --> 23:02.598
conducting experiments
on a confused child.

23:02.642 --> 23:06.994
My client is a devoted
and protective father.

23:07.037 --> 23:09.692
He was desperate
to shield his son

23:09.736 --> 23:12.782
from a radical doctor's
perversions.

23:12.826 --> 23:17.178
He demanded that Bartell
stop treating his son.

23:17.221 --> 23:18.962
Let me say that again--

23:19.006 --> 23:20.442
hisson.

23:20.486 --> 23:24.359
At which point,
Bartell refused,

23:24.403 --> 23:27.318
so my client threatened
to call the police.

23:27.362 --> 23:31.366
Bartell attacked him,
forcing him to defend himself.

23:31.410 --> 23:36.066
And that, ladies and gentlemen,
is what really happened.

23:36.110 --> 23:42.682
♪

23:42.725 --> 23:44.640
- When you interviewed
the defendant,

23:44.684 --> 23:47.469
did he appear to have
any serious injuries?

23:47.513 --> 23:50.472
- No, but I did notice some
scratches on his forearms.

23:50.516 --> 23:54.998
- And uh, did the defendant
tell you how he got scratched?

23:55.042 --> 23:57.479
- He claims it was a stray cat.
- Huh.

23:57.523 --> 23:59.263
He didn't tell you that, uh,

23:59.307 --> 24:01.004
someone threatened his life,
tried to kill him?

24:01.048 --> 24:02.484
- No, he did not.

24:02.528 --> 24:06.270
- Never mentioned that
he was acting in self-defense?

24:06.314 --> 24:07.533
- Never came up.

24:07.576 --> 24:10.013
- And when did
this interview take place?

24:10.057 --> 24:13.669
- Three days after
Dr. Bartell was murdered.

24:13.713 --> 24:17.020
- Thank you.
No further questions.

24:17.064 --> 24:20.850
- Detective, did you recover
a 5-inch-long,

24:20.894 --> 24:24.201
seven-gauge hypodermic needle
from the crime scene?

24:24.245 --> 24:25.551
- It's possible.

24:25.594 --> 24:27.596
We recovered a variety
of medical instruments.

24:27.640 --> 24:30.207
- So that's a yes?

24:30.251 --> 24:31.208
- Sure.

24:33.646 --> 24:38.477
- Was it similar
to this type of needle?

24:38.520 --> 24:39.608
- Similar.

24:41.480 --> 24:44.787
- And would you agree
that a needle like this

24:44.831 --> 24:47.790
would qualify as a weapon?

24:47.834 --> 24:53.274
- I suppose given certain
circumstances, it could.

24:53.317 --> 24:55.798
- And the scratches
on my client's arm

24:55.842 --> 24:57.670
would be consistent
with being assaulted

24:57.713 --> 24:59.541
with this type of needle?
- Objection.

24:59.585 --> 25:00.890
Calls for speculation.

25:00.934 --> 25:02.588
This witness is not
a medical expert.

25:02.631 --> 25:04.285
- Sustained.

25:04.328 --> 25:05.721
- No further questions.

25:05.765 --> 25:07.157
- Court will adjourn
for the day.

25:07.201 --> 25:09.246
The trial will resume
tomorrow at 9:00 a.m.

25:09.290 --> 25:11.118
[gavel bangs]

25:13.947 --> 25:16.384
- Uh, prep Susan Bartell.

25:16.427 --> 25:17.994
She's up first thing tomorrow.

25:24.827 --> 25:25.045
.

25:25.088 --> 25:27.177
- Susan was supposed
to testify tomorrow.

25:27.221 --> 25:28.744
- I know, but she left town.

25:28.788 --> 25:30.572
She said she needed to escape.

25:30.616 --> 25:31.965
- We need her testimony.

25:32.008 --> 25:33.575
- We're trying to prosecute
her brother's killer,

25:33.619 --> 25:34.794
for God's sake.

25:34.837 --> 25:36.926
- Well, as always,
when it's time for her

25:36.970 --> 25:39.320
to step up
and face the consequences

25:39.363 --> 25:40.756
of her so-called activism,

25:40.800 --> 25:42.453
she just dips
into daddy's trust fund

25:42.497 --> 25:43.759
and jets off to Europe.

25:43.803 --> 25:44.891
- What do you mean,
consequences?

25:44.934 --> 25:46.153
- Some of the parents
at the school

25:46.196 --> 25:47.546
are planning to sue her.

25:47.589 --> 25:48.895
- For what?

25:48.938 --> 25:50.200
- Violating their
parental rights

25:50.244 --> 25:52.072
for helping Taylor transition.

25:52.115 --> 25:54.944
I warned Ryan not to get
involved with that kid.

25:54.988 --> 25:57.730
[sighs]

25:57.773 --> 26:00.863
- Wait, you knew your husband
was treating Taylor?

26:00.907 --> 26:02.691
And you didn't tell us?

26:02.735 --> 26:04.867
[tense music]

26:04.911 --> 26:08.175
- If you know anything
that could help our case...

26:08.218 --> 26:14.355
♪

26:14.398 --> 26:17.706
- Myers threatened to kill Ryan
a few months ago.

26:19.186 --> 26:22.537
They had a meeting
at our house, in Ryan's office.

26:22.581 --> 26:24.670
They talked about
the puberty blockers,

26:24.713 --> 26:26.933
the treatments,
the side effects.

26:26.976 --> 26:29.805
Then Myers went nuts.
He started screaming.

26:29.849 --> 26:31.677
I overheard the whole thing.

26:33.156 --> 26:34.984
- We need you to testify.

26:36.072 --> 26:39.249
- Let me guess, you're worried
about your base discovering

26:39.293 --> 26:43.645
that you knew your husband
was treating a trans kid.

26:43.689 --> 26:47.127
- My husband is dead,
and I miss him terribly.

26:47.170 --> 26:49.695
But right now,
I need to worry about me--

26:49.738 --> 26:52.219
my career, my future.

26:52.262 --> 26:55.570
This is the only thing
that I have left.

26:55.614 --> 26:58.225
- Is your career
really that important?

26:58.268 --> 27:00.531
Is it really worth
letting the man

27:00.575 --> 27:03.186
who killed your husband
walk free?

27:03.230 --> 27:10.193
♪

27:13.022 --> 27:14.894
Your husband met
with the Myers.

27:14.937 --> 27:16.460
Could you tell us
about that meeting?

27:16.504 --> 27:19.594
- Ryan knew that it was
in Taylor's best interest

27:19.638 --> 27:21.030
to get the parents on board.

27:21.074 --> 27:23.467
So he sat them down
to assure them that,

27:23.511 --> 27:25.469
in his professional opinion,

27:25.513 --> 27:27.689
gender-affirming care is safe.

27:27.733 --> 27:29.865
- And when did that meeting
take place?

27:29.909 --> 27:32.781
- About two months
before Ryan was killed.

27:32.825 --> 27:36.393
- Did you overhear
the conversation?

27:36.437 --> 27:38.439
- I did.

27:38.482 --> 27:41.529
It got quite heated.

27:41.572 --> 27:45.141
I heard Mr. Myers
screaming at my husband,

27:45.185 --> 27:48.231
calling him horrible names,
threatening him.

27:48.275 --> 27:51.278
- Threatening him?
What were his exact words?

27:52.714 --> 27:54.063
- He said,

27:54.107 --> 27:58.067
"If you lay a hand on my son,
I'll kill you."

28:04.465 --> 28:05.945
- No further questions.

28:10.079 --> 28:13.082
- Congresswoman, you've taken
a very public position

28:13.126 --> 28:16.520
against allowing
trans children to transition.

28:16.564 --> 28:19.480
- Objection. Relevance?

28:19.523 --> 28:20.873
- Goes to credibility.

28:20.916 --> 28:24.050
- The objection is overruled.

28:24.093 --> 28:27.357
- So are you opposed to giving
puberty blockers to children?

28:27.401 --> 28:30.839
Or were you lying,
just saying that to get votes

28:30.883 --> 28:32.928
from your conservative
electorate?

28:32.972 --> 28:35.278
- No, that's what I believe.

28:35.322 --> 28:37.628
- And yet,
those very procedures

28:37.672 --> 28:40.806
were happening
under your own roof?

28:40.849 --> 28:42.546
- They were.

28:42.590 --> 28:44.984
I know, it's--it's crazy,

28:45.027 --> 28:47.813
given this polarized world,
but...

28:49.815 --> 28:51.686
My husband and
I loved each other.

28:53.079 --> 28:55.777
We had a lot in common too.

28:55.821 --> 28:57.605
Except politics.

28:57.648 --> 29:01.740
- Your husband enjoyed
being a doctor, didn't he?

29:01.783 --> 29:03.263
- He did.

29:03.306 --> 29:05.787
He dedicated his life to his
practice, to his patients.

29:05.831 --> 29:09.486
- So it's fair to say
that he had a lot to lose

29:09.530 --> 29:13.882
if Mr. Myers reported
his misconduct to the police?

29:13.926 --> 29:17.233
- If what you're asking is
would Ryan attack someone

29:17.277 --> 29:18.974
over a phone call
to the police,

29:19.018 --> 29:22.848
then the answer
is an emphatic no.

29:22.891 --> 29:27.678
Ryan didn't have
a violent bone in his body.

29:27.722 --> 29:29.202
- No further questions.

29:29.245 --> 29:36.165
♪

29:36.209 --> 29:39.734
- The congresswoman did
a hell of a job today.

29:39.778 --> 29:41.649
- She's a politician.

29:41.692 --> 29:42.998
- Not today.

29:43.042 --> 29:46.262
Today she was a wife
talking from the heart.

29:47.611 --> 29:50.832
- The one thing we still
haven't figured out is,

29:50.876 --> 29:53.530
how did Myers
learn that Bartell

29:53.574 --> 29:55.402
was actually treating Taylor?

29:57.621 --> 30:00.842
We need to dig deeper
into Taylor's doctor visits,

30:00.886 --> 30:03.671
the video
near Bartell's home office.

30:03.714 --> 30:06.717
Maybe Myers or his wife showed
up, created another scene.

30:06.761 --> 30:08.067
- Yeah, I get it.

30:08.110 --> 30:09.938
But why are you so unsure?

30:09.982 --> 30:11.722
- I'm not unsure of the case.

30:11.766 --> 30:14.856
[chuckles]
I'm unsure of the jury.

30:14.900 --> 30:16.902
Do they really
wanna convict Myers

30:16.945 --> 30:19.382
for protecting his child?

30:21.297 --> 30:23.169
- Just wondering
if you're worried

30:23.212 --> 30:25.127
because that's how you feel.

30:27.869 --> 30:29.479
- If I'm being
completely honest,

30:29.523 --> 30:32.395
the idea of a child being
allowed to make

30:32.439 --> 30:34.876
such a huge decision
at age 13--

30:34.920 --> 30:37.009
that makes me uncomfortable.

30:37.052 --> 30:39.707
- I'm not sure it's a decision.

30:39.750 --> 30:40.882
- What does that mean?

30:40.926 --> 30:42.753
- Taylor has known who she is

30:42.797 --> 30:44.277
since she was old enough
to talk.

30:44.320 --> 30:46.105
- She's a kid.

30:46.148 --> 30:48.498
Right now, she thinks
she knows who she is.

30:48.542 --> 30:49.935
What about in five years?

30:49.978 --> 30:51.937
I didn't have
a half a clue about anything

30:51.980 --> 30:53.286
when I was 13 years old.

30:53.329 --> 30:56.202
- There's a difference
between not knowing

30:56.245 --> 30:59.074
if you wanna be an astronaut
or a firefighter

30:59.118 --> 31:02.904
when you grow up,
and not knowing who you are.

31:02.948 --> 31:05.515
You never felt like
you weren't a boy.

31:05.559 --> 31:08.605
Imagine being trapped
in a female body,

31:08.649 --> 31:09.955
forced to grow boobs.

31:11.913 --> 31:15.482
I'm just saying,
it's complicated.

31:18.398 --> 31:19.312
- Yeah.

31:23.838 --> 31:26.754
It says here, Susan Bartell

31:26.797 --> 31:28.887
pulled Taylor out
of class three times

31:28.930 --> 31:30.627
to meet with her brother.
- Okay.

31:30.671 --> 31:36.677
- But we know Taylor visited
with Dr. Bartell four times.

31:36.720 --> 31:39.158
- Susan Bartell was out sick

31:39.201 --> 31:42.117
the day Taylor had
her fourth appointment.

31:42.161 --> 31:45.207
- So if Susan
wasn't in school,

31:45.251 --> 31:47.470
how did Taylor get out
of class?

31:50.560 --> 31:52.345
You wrote a permission slip

31:52.388 --> 31:53.868
so Taylor could go see
Dr. Bartell.

31:53.912 --> 31:54.825
- I thought it was
for a checkup.

31:54.869 --> 31:56.305
- You're lying.

31:56.349 --> 31:58.438
You and your husband had
already met with Dr. Bartell.

31:58.481 --> 32:01.049
You knew the kind of treatment
he wanted to provide.

32:09.014 --> 32:12.321
- After the scene Robert made,

32:12.365 --> 32:14.497
Bartell refused to give Taylor
the medication.

32:14.541 --> 32:15.977
He--he didn't wanna
break the law.

32:16.021 --> 32:17.979
He knew we didn't approve.

32:18.023 --> 32:20.112
And Taylor got
really upset, so I--

32:20.155 --> 32:23.854
- So you gave Bartell consent
to treat Taylor?

32:23.898 --> 32:26.683
[apprehensive music]

32:26.727 --> 32:30.078
- [sighs]

32:30.122 --> 32:33.647
- [exhales]
You need to testify.

32:33.690 --> 32:35.910
Tell the jury that
Bartell had your approval.

32:35.954 --> 32:38.043
- No, no, I--I can't.

32:38.086 --> 32:40.349
- If your husband walks free,

32:40.393 --> 32:42.873
he'll continue to fight
Taylor's transition.

32:42.917 --> 32:45.006
He'll file lawsuits,
injunctions.

32:45.050 --> 32:48.009
Think what that
will do to Taylor.

32:48.053 --> 32:50.533
You have a choice to make.

32:50.577 --> 32:53.188
Who do you want to protect,
your husband...

32:55.147 --> 32:56.713
Or your daughter?

32:56.757 --> 32:58.193
- Mom?

33:00.935 --> 33:03.198
Is everything okay?

33:06.462 --> 33:08.725
- Yes, sweetheart.

33:08.769 --> 33:11.076
Everything is fine.

33:11.119 --> 33:17.299
♪

33:17.343 --> 33:20.999
- Taylor was in so much pain
that I prayed for a way

33:21.042 --> 33:23.044
to make it stop.

33:23.088 --> 33:26.265
And I had to accept that
this was the answer.

33:26.308 --> 33:30.312
- So you authorized Dr. Bartell
to treat Taylor?

33:30.356 --> 33:32.053
- Yes.

33:32.097 --> 33:34.577
And I forged
Robert's signature.

33:34.621 --> 33:41.323
♪

33:41.976 --> 33:45.501
But you have to understand,
I was terrified that he'd--

33:45.545 --> 33:47.634
that she'd try to--

33:52.726 --> 33:57.774
- Your husband claimed
that Dr. Bartell attacked him

33:57.818 --> 34:00.560
to cover up the doctor's crime

34:00.603 --> 34:03.215
of treating Taylor
without parental consent.

34:03.258 --> 34:08.089
But Bartell wasn't
committing a crime, because...

34:08.132 --> 34:10.483
you gave him permission.

34:10.525 --> 34:14.094
- I--I felt like
we kept getting it wrong.

34:14.139 --> 34:16.750
That no matter
what choice we made,

34:16.793 --> 34:19.274
it was hurting Taylor.

34:19.318 --> 34:21.449
And I just wanted
to make sure that

34:21.494 --> 34:23.148
she didn't try
to hurt herself again.

34:23.190 --> 34:30.329
♪

34:31.721 --> 34:36.030
I'm sorry, but I thought
it was better to support

34:36.074 --> 34:38.293
our daughter than to--

34:38.337 --> 34:41.295
than to mourn the death
of our son.

34:43.429 --> 34:48.650
And I was just so scared
she was going to hurt herself.

34:48.695 --> 34:51.741
Yes, she.

34:51.784 --> 34:53.699
I--I needed to embrace her.

34:55.527 --> 34:56.833
Love her.

34:56.877 --> 34:59.227
[weeping]

35:02.187 --> 35:03.405
- No further questions.

35:07.192 --> 35:08.758
- We have no questions.

35:08.802 --> 35:10.108
- The people rest.

35:10.151 --> 35:16.418
♪

35:16.462 --> 35:18.768
- Does the defense plan
on calling any witnesses?

35:18.812 --> 35:21.554
- Yes. We call Taylor Myers.

35:21.597 --> 35:23.512
- What?

35:23.556 --> 35:24.731
- No.

35:24.774 --> 35:25.949
You can't call Taylor
to the stand.

35:25.993 --> 35:27.081
It will destroy her.

35:29.083 --> 35:30.215
- Your Honor,
the people object.

35:30.258 --> 35:31.694
- Based on what?

35:31.738 --> 35:35.089
The defense has the right
to call witnesses.

35:35.133 --> 35:36.438
- I agree.

35:36.482 --> 35:38.266
Court will resume
tomorrow morning.

35:38.310 --> 35:39.702
[gavel bangs]

35:39.746 --> 35:46.318
♪

35:52.237 --> 35:52.411
.

35:52.454 --> 35:54.195
- Mr. Price, please.

35:54.239 --> 35:55.283
You can't let them put
Taylor on the stand.

35:55.327 --> 35:56.719
- I would like to help,

35:56.763 --> 35:59.200
but the court has ruled,
and I have to comply.

35:59.244 --> 36:01.028
- You don't understand.

36:01.071 --> 36:03.422
Taylor is very fragile.

36:06.251 --> 36:09.079
She can't withstand
this kind of pressure.

36:09.123 --> 36:10.864
- I assure you,
my cross-examination

36:10.907 --> 36:13.388
will be respectful.

36:13.432 --> 36:15.477
- I'm scared she might try
to kill herself.

36:17.784 --> 36:19.220
Please.

36:19.264 --> 36:20.961
There must be something
you can do.

36:27.185 --> 36:30.057
- You could try to have
her declared incompetent.

36:30.100 --> 36:32.277
- But she's 13, not 3.

36:32.320 --> 36:34.235
I don't think any credible
psychiatrist will find

36:34.279 --> 36:35.932
that she's unable
to tell the difference

36:35.976 --> 36:37.412
between the truth and a lie.

36:37.456 --> 36:39.719
- What about incompetent based
on mental health reasons?

36:39.762 --> 36:41.416
- No, I've looked into it.

36:41.460 --> 36:44.158
Unfortunately, suicidal
ideation isn't a valid basis.

36:44.202 --> 36:47.596
- The other option
is to offer Myers a plea.

36:47.640 --> 36:49.468
- Our case is strong.

36:49.511 --> 36:53.211
And Dr. Bartell was a good man.

36:53.254 --> 36:55.604
He was doing his job,
trying to help Taylor,

36:55.648 --> 36:56.953
and he deserves justice.

36:56.997 --> 36:58.564
- To what end?

36:58.607 --> 37:01.044
Is it worth
sacrificing the future

37:01.088 --> 37:02.611
of a young, innocent kid?

37:02.655 --> 37:05.092
- I have empathy for Taylor,
but let's not lose track

37:05.135 --> 37:06.049
of who our victim is.

37:06.093 --> 37:07.790
- I agree.

37:07.834 --> 37:09.618
But putting Taylor on the stand

37:09.662 --> 37:11.620
presents a credible risk
to our case.

37:11.664 --> 37:14.797
And if she breaks down,
it could bolster the argument

37:14.841 --> 37:16.277
that she wasn't old enough

37:16.321 --> 37:17.583
to make any of these decisions
herself,

37:17.626 --> 37:21.064
or that medication's
screwing her up.

37:21.108 --> 37:24.633
- In which case,
Myers will walk,

37:24.677 --> 37:27.984
and we'll have traumatized
an innocent child for nothing.

37:28.028 --> 37:30.944
[tense music]

37:30.987 --> 37:38.125
♪

37:41.694 --> 37:43.913
- Your client pleads guilty
to murder two.

37:43.957 --> 37:45.785
We'll recommend 25 years.

37:45.828 --> 37:47.917
- Man one. 15 years.

37:47.961 --> 37:49.310
- Not gonna happen.

37:49.354 --> 37:50.790
- He realizes
he's facing life, right?

37:50.833 --> 37:53.575
- I'm happy to finish
the trial, roll the dice.

37:53.619 --> 37:56.012
- Uh, your odds of winning
are not very good.

37:56.056 --> 37:57.231
Ask your lawyer.

37:57.275 --> 37:58.363
- If you were really
that confident,

37:58.406 --> 37:59.538
you wouldn't be here.

38:01.583 --> 38:05.370
- We're here because we're
worried about your daughter.

38:05.413 --> 38:08.373
- We're trying to spare
your child the humiliation

38:08.416 --> 38:11.289
of being forced to defend
her personhood

38:11.332 --> 38:13.247
in front of a group
of strangers.

38:16.119 --> 38:19.688
- Man one. 15 years.

38:19.732 --> 38:21.908
- You're really willing
to hold your daughter's

38:21.951 --> 38:24.214
mental health hostage?

38:24.258 --> 38:27.435
Gamble with her future
over a goddamn plea deal?

38:27.479 --> 38:32.353
- I was trying to save my
child's life, simple as that.

38:32.397 --> 38:35.051
You keep saying daughter.

38:35.095 --> 38:37.227
I don't have a daughter.

38:37.271 --> 38:43.799
♪

38:49.849 --> 38:51.459
- A plea deal?

38:51.503 --> 38:53.853
You're telling me that the
man that murdered my husband

38:53.896 --> 38:56.116
is getting 15 years?

38:56.159 --> 38:57.857
That's what Ryan's life
was worth?

38:57.900 --> 38:59.249
- No. No.

38:59.293 --> 39:03.210
Your husband cared deeply
for his patients.

39:03.253 --> 39:05.125
He risked everything
to care for Taylor.

39:05.168 --> 39:07.823
He would appreciate--
- No.

39:07.867 --> 39:10.260
No. You promised me.

39:10.304 --> 39:12.262
- [sighs]
I'm just trying to protect--

39:12.306 --> 39:14.656
- The trans kid.
Yeah, I get it.

39:14.700 --> 39:18.051
You chose politics
over justice.

39:18.094 --> 39:19.531
- No, that's not fair.

39:19.574 --> 39:22.011
- Oh, you--you begged me
to get on the stand,

39:22.055 --> 39:24.840
to sacrifice my career
in the name of justice,

39:24.884 --> 39:28.104
and you sell me out
for one transgender child?

39:28.148 --> 39:30.324
No, that isn't fair.

39:32.544 --> 39:34.023
[scoffs]

39:34.067 --> 39:36.983
My primary opponent is already
running attack ads

39:37.026 --> 39:39.420
claiming that I support
genital mutilation.

39:39.464 --> 39:41.422
- [scoffs]
That is all the more reason

39:41.466 --> 39:43.903
to protect kids like Taylor.

39:43.946 --> 39:45.687
- You don't get it.

39:49.648 --> 39:52.955
Thanks to you, I will likely
be replaced by someone

39:52.999 --> 39:57.482
who doesn't even believe
that trans people are real,

39:57.525 --> 40:00.310
that it's all make-believe.

40:00.354 --> 40:03.357
So the only thing that
you've accomplished here

40:03.401 --> 40:06.491
is making the world less safe
for those children.

40:10.364 --> 40:13.019
Now get the hell
out of my house.

40:13.062 --> 40:20.200
♪

40:30.950 --> 40:33.909
[dramatic music]

40:33.953 --> 40:40.873
♪

41:00.980 --> 41:03.896
[wolf howls]
